                <article class="news-article">
                    <header class="article-header">
                        <h1 class="article-title">Coffee with a Cop: Building Community at Jackson Laboratory</h1>
                        <div class="article-meta">
                            <span class="article-date"><i class="far fa-calendar-alt"></i> April 16, 2025</span>
                            <span class="article-category"><i class="fas fa-tag"></i> Community</span>
                        </div>
                    </header>
                    <div class="article-featured-image" style="max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto;">
                        <img src="../images/misc/coffeecop.jpg" alt="Coffee with a Cop event at Jackson Laboratory" class="full-width-image">
                        <p class="image-caption">Bar Harbor Mount Desert Police Department and Jackson Laboratory staff connect over coffee and conversation.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="article-content">
                        <p>The Bar Harbor Mount Desert Police Department, in coordination with the Jackson Laboratory, hosted a Coffee with a Cop event this morning on the Bar Harbor Campus. These events are a great opportunity for our employees to meet people and answer lots of questions.</p>
                        <p>Officers and staff from both organizations enjoyed meaningful conversations, shared stories, and addressed a variety of questions from attendees. Events like these help foster trust, transparency, and positive relationships between law enforcement and the community we serve.</p>
                        <blockquote>
                            <p>"A big thanks to Jackson Lab for having us! Please keep an eye out for other Coffee with a Cop events coming in the near future!"</p>
                        </blockquote>
                        <p>The department encourages everyone to join us at future Coffee with a Cop events for a chance to connect, ask questions, and enjoy a cup of coffee together.</p>
                    </div>
